data.meta_description: Built by Wm. Mason Feb. 22, 1869 as Boston, Lowell & Nashua No. 20. (Cons. No. 304). To B&L No. 20 BILLERICA, c1878. To B&M (pre-1911) No. 320 (1st), Class A, c1887. Cylinders 16x24. Scrapped Concord, N.H. Sep. 1, 1905. Billerica is a town in Middlesex County, Massachusetts. data.text:
Built by Wm. Mason Feb. 22, 1869 as Boston, Lowell & Nashua No. 20. (Cons. No. 304). To B&L No. 20 BILLERICA, c1878. To B&M (pre-1911) No. 320 (1st), Class A, c1887. Cylinders 16x24. Scrapped Concord, N.H. Sep. 1, 1905. Billerica is a town in Middlesex County, Massachusetts.

Digital image made from photograph in Boston & Maine Railroad Historical Society Archives. Cat. No. 1998.12. Gift of Kenneth F. McCall Estate. Copyright Boston & Maine Railroad Historical Society, Inc. Learn more about the B&MRRHS at www.bmrrhs.org. Photo 1848
